Police say that at least 200 students barricaded roads leading to the Pretoria campus and set fire to the guard house. JOHANNESBURG Management at the Tshwane University of Technology (TUT) are currently in a meeting with student leaders and public order policing officers following a night of violent protests on the main campus.Police say at least 200 students barricaded roads leading to the Pretoria campus and set fire to the guard house.It s understood the students are unhappy about accommodation issues.The campus remains shut for the day due to safety concerns.The police's Sally De Beer: The public order police persuaded them to negotiate further with TUT management and to have over memorandum. No police action was taken and it s calm at the moment. The negotiations are continuing. LISTEN: Sporadic incidents of violence at TUT(Edited by Tamsin Wort)